TITLE: Using Message Placeholders in context.report() in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use placeholders in the message and provide data for dynamic content in the error message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/main/docs/src/extend/custom-rules.md#2025-04-14_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
context.report({
    node: node,
    message: "Unexpected identifier: {{ identifier }}",
    data: {
        identifier: node.name
    }
});
```

