TITLE: Including .gitignore Patterns in ESLint Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to include patterns from a .gitignore file in the ESLint configuration using the @eslint/compat package. It loads the .gitignore file and translates its patterns into ESLint ignore rules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/main/docs/src/use/configure/ignore.md#2025-04-14_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// eslint.config.js
import { defineConfig } from "eslint/config";
import { includeIgnoreFile } from "@eslint/compat";
import { fileURLToPath } from "node:url";

const gitignorePath = fileURLToPath(new URL(".gitignore", import.meta.url));

export default defineConfig([
	includeIgnoreFile(gitignorePath),
	{
		// your overrides
	},
]);
```

