TITLE: Demonstrating Correct Usage of Declarations in Switch Statements (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet illustrates the correct way to use declarations in switch statements. It shows how to wrap case clauses in blocks to limit the scope of lexical declarations, demonstrates valid var usage due to function-scope hoisting, and includes an example of a valid declaration outside the switch statement.
