TITLE: Demonstrating Return Override in Finally Block (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how a return statement in a finally block overrides a return statement in a try block. Instead of returning 1 as expected, the function returns 3.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/main/docs/src/rules/no-unsafe-finally.md#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// We expect this function to return 1;
(() => {
    try {
        return 1; // 1 is returned but suspended until finally block ends
    } catch(err) {
        return 2;
    } finally {
        return 3; // 3 is returned before 1, which we did not expect
    }
})();

// > 3
```

