TITLE: Specifying ESLint Processor from Plugin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to specify a processor from an ESLint plugin. It configures the markdown processor for Markdown files and sets up additional configurations for JavaScript code blocks within Markdown files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/main/docs/src/use/configure/plugins.md#2025-04-14_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// eslint.config.js
import markdown from "@eslint/markdown";
import { defineConfig } from "eslint/config";

export default defineConfig([
	// applies to all JavaScript files
	{
		rules: {
			strict: "error",
		},
	},

	// applies to Markdown files
	{
		files: ["**/*.md"],
		plugins: {
			markdown,
		},
		processor: "markdown/markdown",
	},

	// applies only to JavaScript blocks inside of Markdown files
	{
		files: ["**/*.md/*.js"],
		rules: {
			strict: "off",
		},
	},
]);
```

