TITLE: Demonstrating Error Suppression in Finally Block (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how a return statement in a finally block suppresses an error thrown in a try block. Instead of propagating the error, the function returns 3.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/main/docs/src/rules/no-unsafe-finally.md#2025-04-14_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// We expect this function to throw an error, then return
(() => {
    try {
        throw new Error("Try"); // error is thrown but suspended until finally block ends
    } finally {
        return 3; // 3 is returned before the error is thrown, which we did not expect
    }
})();

// > 3
```

