TITLE: Demonstrating Break Override in Finally Block (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how a break statement in a finally block can break out of a labeled try-finally block before the return value from the try block is processed, resulting in an unexpected return value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/main/docs/src/rules/no-unsafe-finally.md#2025-04-14_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// We expect this function to return 0 from try block.
(() => {
  label: try {
    return 0; // 0 is returned but suspended until finally block ends
  } finally {
    break label; // It breaks out the try-finally block, before 0 is returned.
  }
  return 1;
})();

// > 1
```

