TITLE: Incorrect Usage Examples of Backreferences in JavaScript RegExp
DESCRIPTION: This code block demonstrates multiple examples of incorrect usages of backreferences in regular expressions that are flagged by the ESLint rule, including references to groups in another alternative, forward references, nested references, and references to groups in negative lookarounds.
