TITLE: Demonstrating Error Override in Finally Block (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how a throw statement in a finally block overrides an error thrown in a catch block. Instead of propagating the original error, a new error from the finally block is thrown.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/main/docs/src/rules/no-unsafe-finally.md#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// We expect this function to throw Try(...) error from the catch block
(() => {
    try {
        throw new Error("Try")
    } catch(err) {
        throw err; // The error thrown from try block is caught and rethrown
    } finally {
        throw new Error("Finally"); // Finally(...) is thrown, which we did not expect
    }
})();

// > Uncaught Error: Finally(...)
```

