TITLE: Correct code examples for 'never' option
DESCRIPTION: Examples of code that correctly follows the object-curly-newline rule when configured with the 'never' option, showing proper formatting without line breaks at braces.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/main/docs/src/rules/object-curly-newline.md#2025-04-14_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
/*eslint object-curly-newline: ["error", "never"]*/

let a = {};
let b = {foo: 1};
let c = {foo: 1, bar: 2};
let d = {foo: 1,
    bar: 2};
let e = {foo: function() {
    dosomething();
}};

let {} = obj;
let {f} = obj;
let {g, h} = obj;
let {i,
    j} = obj;
let {k = function() {
    dosomething();
}} = obj;
```

